update-notifier (0.99.3debian7) unstable; urgency=low

  * src/update-notifier:
    - Use 'sudo' group instead of 'admin' group (Closes: #502392)
    - If 'sudo' contains no members, treat every user as an admin.
  * src/reboot.c: Reboot fixes (Closes: #594220)
    - reboot via GNOME Session: use Shutdown() instead of RequestReboot()
    - reboot via HAL: Replace by ConsoleKit approach (Closes: #604530)
  * Display currently active transactions even for normal users.
  * Correctly detect Debian security updates (Closes: #493653).

 -- Julian Andres Klode <jak@debian.org>  Mon, 22 Nov 2010 19:53:45 +0100

update-notifier (0.99.3debian6) unstable; urgency=low

  * Replaces/Breaks old update-notifier-common (Closes: #590605).
  * Update Standards-Version to 3.9.1.
  * Use architecture wildcards (Closes: #587867).
  * Do not recommend cpu-checker (Closes: #587437).
  * data/update-motd-updates-available:
    - Correctly handle sources.list.d and sources.list (Closes: #586438).
  * debian/15update-stamp:
    - Use Post-Invoke instead of Post-Invoke-Success (Closes: #584682).
  * src/reboot.c:
    - Do not log error that org.debian.apt is not provided (Closes: #583698).
  * Update Czech translation (Closes: #590705) [although translations should
    normally be done in Launchpad for increased collaboration].

 -- Julian Andres Klode <jak@debian.org>  Mon, 02 Aug 2010 15:11:42 +0200

